2026-03-22 19:05:57,726 - INFO - AI Response: Namaste! You're asking about Article 21 of the Indian Constitution. It's one of the most important fundamental rights we have.

Article 21 states that "No person shall be deprived of his life or personal liberty except according to procedure established by law."

In simple words, it guarantees everyone the Right to Life and Personal Liberty. The Supreme Court has interpreted this very broadly over the years to include many other rights essential for a dignified life, such as:

   The right to live with human dignity
   The right to a clean environment
   The right to privacy
   The right to education
   The right to a speedy trial
   The right to livelihood

It essentially means that the state cannot take away your life or freedom unless it follows a fair, just, and reasonable legal procedure.

Is there anything specific about Article 21 that you would like to know more about?
